---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BusinessCard from '../components/BusinessCard.astro';
import IconStrip from '../components/IconStrip.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — probl.me"
  description="I'm Richard, a cybersecurity and SaaS product manager building personal projects with AI and writing about what I learn."
>

  <!-- ─── INTRO + CARD ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="intro">
    <div class="intro-text">
      <div class="eyebrow">// about</div>
      <h1 class="intro-h1">Hi, I'm Richard.<br />I build in public.</h1>
      <p class="intro-sub">
        I work in cybersecurity and SaaS product management, and on the side I
        tinker on personal projects with AI, writing down what I learn as I go.
        probl.me is that notebook, kept in the open.
      </p>
    </div>

    <BusinessCard variant="about" />
  </section>

  <!-- ─── STORY ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <article class="prose-wrap">
    <h2>Why this blog exists</h2>
    <p>
      I learn best by building the real thing and writing down what happened. Most
      posts about working with AI are either hype or fear. I wanted a third option:
      an honest log from someone actually shipping, including the parts that did not
      work.
    </p>
    <p>
      So probl.me runs on the same principles I write about. The site is a static
      <a href="/blog?tag=astro">Astro</a> build on GitHub Pages, the content moves
      through a pipeline of Claude agents, and every decision is documented. The
      process is the subject as much as the output.
    </p>

    <h2>What I'm building now</h2>
    <p>
      Two things, in parallel. probl.me is the blog you're reading. Celly is a
      sister product I'm developing alongside it. Both are early, both are public,
      and both show up in what I write here.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you're a PM curious about AI, a developer figuring out how to work with
      agents, or someone non-technical who wants to manage their own software
      projects, I'm writing for you.
    </p>
  </article>

  <!-- ─── ICON STRIP ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <IconStrip />

  <!-- ─── CTA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cta">
    <h2 class="cta-h2">Read along, or reach out</h2>
    <p class="cta-sub">
      New posts twice a week. If something here is useful or wrong, I'd genuinely
      like to hear it.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-btns">
      <Button href="/blog" variant="primary">Read the blog</Button>
      <Button href="https://github.com/rustymuffler" variant="secondary" external>Follow on GitHub</Button>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
/* ── Intro ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.intro {
  max-width: var(--max-width);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 72px 32px 40px;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 0.9fr;
  gap: 64px;
  align-items: start;
}

.eyebrow {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.intro-h1 {
  font-size: 44px;
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  line-height: 1.1;
  margin: 16px 0 0;
}

.intro-sub {
  font-size: 18px;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin: 20px 0 0;
}

/* ── Story prose ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
.prose-wrap {
  max-width: var(--reading-width);
  margin: 24px auto 0;
  padding: 0 24px;
  font-size: 18px;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: #E9E1D3;
}

.prose-wrap h2 {
  font-size: 26px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  margin: 40px 0 0;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

.prose-wrap h2:first-child {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.prose-wrap p {
  margin: 1.2em 0 0;
}

.prose-wrap a {
  color: var(--color-amber);
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(242, 162, 75, 0.35);
}

.prose-wrap a:hover {
  border-bottom-color: var(--color-amber);
}

/* ── CTA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cta {
  max-width: var(--reading-width);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 64px 24px 24px;
  text-align: center;
}

.cta-h2 {
  font-size: 26px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  margin: 0;
}

.cta-sub {
  font-size: 16px;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin: 12px 0 0;
}

.cta-btns {
  display: flex;
  gap: 14px;
  justify-content: center;
  margin-top: 26px;
}
</style>
